hands_on_practices.solution:
1. Relevant flow equations:
$$\frac{dg_s}{d\ell}=-A\,g_s^2 - B\,g_p^2,\quad \frac{dg_p}{d\ell}=-C\,g_s g_p + D\,g_p^2.$$
2. Define $R=g_p/g_s$. Then
$$\frac{dR}{d\ell}
=\frac{g_s\,\frac{dg_p}{d\ell}-g_p\,\frac{dg_s}{d\ell}}{g_s^2}
=\frac{-C\,g_s^2g_p +D\,g_sg_p^2 +A\,g_s^2g_p +B\,g_p^3}{g_s^2}.$$
3. Simplify using $g_p=R\,g_s$:
$$\frac{dR}{d\ell}
=R(A-C)+D\,R^2 +B\,R^3\big)\,g_s.$$
4. With $d\ell_R=g_s\,d\ell$, the beta function is
$$\beta_R=\frac{dR}{d\ell_R}=\frac{1}{g_s}\frac{dR}{d\ell}
=(A-C)R + D\,R^2 + B\,R^3.$$
